text.tspan: 1. Make 5 TREES each consisting of 3 different colour pieces
2. Place 1 on the centre space and 1 on each corner space of the BOARD
3. Deal 2 random GOAL CARDS privately to each player
4. Place remaining GOAL CARDS in a face down pile
TREE: A stack of 3 pieces, SMALL on top of MEDIUM on top of LARGE
Move the topmost piece on a square 1 space in a MARKED DIRECTION,
stacking on top of any pieces already in that square
The stack on any square contains, in order with no intervening pieces,
the 3 pieces shown on a GOAL CARD currently held by either player
Holder of the GOAL CARD wins
Replace either of your GOAL CARDS
with any GOAL CARD from the pile, without looking
A player may win at any time, including during their opponent's turn
For edge squares, clockwise or inward to the centre square
For the centre square, outward to any edge square
